British singer Rita Ora is in Kenya to celebrate her birthday. In a series of posts, the 27 year-old documented her stay in Kenya, including a day spent with children in a Maasai village. "I've never been sang a song like this for my birthday before. I went to a beautiful Masai Village and they were so welcoming and my energy and soul will never be the same again. Thank you. Best birthday ever!! Also watch until the end I think I found a future superstar! Thank you" The '"Body on Me" hit maker also shared other pictures capturing the vast beauty of the Maasai Mara. Rita Ora is a British singer and actress. She rose to prominence in February 2012 when she featured on DJ Fresh's single "Hot Right Now", which reached number one in the UK. Her debut studio album, Ora, released in August 2012, debuted at number one in the United Kingdom. In 2015, Ora became a coach on the fourth series of The Voice UK and, later that year, a judge on the twelfth series of The X Factor.